<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - WEST COAST MAGNUM MIRRORS AND AERO MIRRORS - DESCRIPTION -
        AERO TUBULAR MIRROR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AERO TUBULAR MIRROR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Each Aero Tubular mirror assembly includes a flat and a convex mirror mounted in a common head which
            attaches to a door mounted "C" loop assembly similar to the West Coast Magnum. The flat glass and the convex
            mirror are heated. Only the flat glass may be motorized. The convex mirror snaps into a manually adjustable
            mounting gimbal. Connection to the cab wire harness is made at the lower "C" loop mounting similar to the
            West Coast Tubular mirror.
        </para>
        <para>An Aero Tubular mirror may be serviced as a complete unit replacement, or individual components may be
            replaced as shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602803">Figure 3</hotlnk>
            and the Service Parts list below.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The lower "C" loop mounting incorporates an internal pre-loaded spring which holds the mirror in
                    one of three detent positions - full forward, driver use or full rear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Do not attempt to disassemble or otherwise tamper with the lower mounting and pivot mechanism.
                    Serious injury may result.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
